title: For Sale:  RARE LARGE FRAME COLT LIGHTNING EXPRESS 40-60-260
postcontent: I have a rare Large Frame Colt Lightning Express Slide Action rifle chambered in the 40-60-260 caliber. This rifle, serial #353 was manufactured in 1887, which is the first year of production. It comes with a Colt Factory letter confirming its original configuration. The letter states that the gun was shipped to E.C. Meacham Arms Company, St. Louis, Missouri on September 9th of 1887 with 10 rifles total in shipment. Being that the gun was sent to St. Louis shows this rifle was one of the arms that was on its way to the western frontier. There were only 6,496 of these big rifles produced during the period of 1887 to 1894 as compared to nearly 90,000 rifles produced for the medium and small frame Lightning's. Then comparing the small number of large frame Lightning rifles to the numbers of Winchester Model 1886 and the Marlin models 1881 and 1895, which all numbered into the hundred of thousands, one can understand just how rare the large frame Lightning really is.Not looking for trades but will consider shipping if needed.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1924 Colt Transition 1911 .45
postcontent: I have for sale a 1924 colt transition 1911 .45.  This gun has been verified as a 1924 from Colt, and is in great shape for an almost 100 year old gun.  It is one of 4,999 that were produced nickle plated.  In the transition period Col produced 10,000 blued, and 4,999 nickle plated 1911 the 10,000 were strictly for the military, but since Colt didn't have a contract to produce the 1911 Government .45 til 1938 this period is now known as the "Transition" period.  This gun is all original minus a firing pin that was upgraded to a 1938 stainless steel.  This is a collectors dream, and need to go.  They sell for 10,000 plus on some government auction sites, and are truly a RARE find.  I am open to partial trades.
